<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/23663744-d-elliott"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1455142906i/23663744._UY100_CR16,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/23663744-d-elliott">D.elliott</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">We learn of Aranka&apos;s fate, for the better or worse: I think this will be dealt with at the beginning of the second series. In terms of difference, it&apos;<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">We learn of Aranka's fate, for the better or worse: I think this will be dealt with at the beginning of the second series. In terms of difference, it's hard to say because I am aware there are fantasy-dystopian novels out there, but my tastes tend to lean more towards the sci-fi dystopias, so I'm not really the best person to judge. However, 'The Soul and the Seed' is a dystopia set in present day which does give the story a unique twist and perhaps makes the reader confront the idea our own world is saturated with corrupting forces and far from ideal. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
