<div id="review_1035888940" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1035888940" />
    <a title="Ember" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/34282923-ember"><img alt="Ember" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1035888940?book_show_action=true">Aug 24, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ember" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ember" href="/user/show/34282923-ember">Ember</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1035888940" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6933978385032387413">I am pulled in to the lives of the characters... Even when I am not reading I am constantly daydreaming about the characters and imagining what they will do next. The book is so well written and the premise and plot are very cleverly planned out. The layers of knowledge and subplots are breathtaking. It&apos;s one of those books where you love to read it over again and you get something new out of it every time you read it. I highly recommend this to realistic people who can tolerate more than just s</span>
  <span id="freeText6933978385032387413" style="display:none">I am pulled in to the lives of the characters... Even when I am not reading I am constantly daydreaming about the characters and imagining what they will do next. The book is so well written and the premise and plot are very cleverly planned out. The layers of knowledge and subplots are breathtaking. It's one of those books where you love to read it over again and you get something new out of it every time you read it. I highly recommend this to realistic people who can tolerate more than just surface fantasy, like Twilight or The Hunger Games. I can't even compare this to any other book because there's never been anything quite like it. I can't wait till this book makes it globally and gets translated to different languages! All I can say is that I highly recommend it.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="6933978385032387413" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


