<span id="freeTextContainer9584460566580552335">ENDING!!!!! God, just all the feels!<br/><br/>Calm now... kinda.<br/><br/>I debated between 4 and 5 stars for this book but in the end, I loved the story so 5 stars it gets.<br/><br/>The world concept in this book is fantastic. I&apos;ve read a lot of totalitarian leaderships in YA dystopian fiction but this is truely unique. The leaders of the world use a form of mind control to influence the masses, those that oppose the ruling powers are either the descendants of an ancient magical race of mages or their followers. I&apos;ve never </span>
  <span id="freeText9584460566580552335" style="display:none">ENDING!!!!! God, just all the feels!<br /><br />Calm now... kinda.<br /><br />I debated between 4 and 5 stars for this book but in the end, I loved the story so 5 stars it gets.<br /><br />The world concept in this book is fantastic. I've read a lot of totalitarian leaderships in YA dystopian fiction but this is truely unique. The leaders of the world use a form of mind control to influence the masses, those that oppose the ruling powers are either the descendants of an ancient magical race of mages or their followers. I've never read anything like this and it hooked me right in.<br /><br />The experiements on the children were just awful and it broke my heart to see them suffer, I'm so glad Aranka survived. She had a quiet bravery about her that I really liked. She wasn't some uber confident super girl or a natural leader, she's just trying to survive and protect what remains of her people. <br /><br />Without giving anything away, I yelled and cursed at the ending... not because it was bad, but because I didn't want it to end. I really enjoyed this book and I'm very glad I've read it.<br /><br /><br />*This book was provided to me by the author in exchange for an honest review.</span>
