        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1078361807" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6262353391706427042">The only thing that robs this of a fifth star is that I thought it started somewhat slowly. Don&apos;t let that stop you! Read through the slow start and you will be rewarded. <br/><br/>This is set in the Pacific Northwest. I&apos;ve been there in the Kootenays, so I could visualize the area clearly. The characters are clearly drawn and Farnam is not afraid to kill them off - a bonus, since they are described early and often as being in danger. She isn&apos;t graphic most of the time, but she&apos;s good about showing the fa</span>
  <span id="freeText6262353391706427042" style="display:none">The only thing that robs this of a fifth star is that I thought it started somewhat slowly. Don't let that stop you! Read through the slow start and you will be rewarded. <br /><br />This is set in the Pacific Northwest. I've been there in the Kootenays, so I could visualize the area clearly. The characters are clearly drawn and Farnam is not afraid to kill them off - a bonus, since they are described early and often as being in danger. She isn't graphic most of the time, but she's good about showing the fact that the danger is real.<br /><br />Farnam is also good at worldbuilding. This is based in a world very like our own twenty minutes from now, but most of the time the characters are not dealing with the day-to-day world as we know it. She has thought about languages, about why her diverse cast has come together, and she's taken care that no one is a Mary Sue. <br /><br />I am looking forward to the sequel! Don't let my slightly-lower number of stars scare you off. This is a good book!</span>
  <a data-text-id="6262353391706427042" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

